does not comprehend this empirical and specific reality of symbolization depending on pre-existing transcendental conditions. Instead, he proceeds from the empirical diversity of the symbolisations and reflects on their simultaneously general and specific conditions. Thus, Cassirer embarks on a path that he finds paved in Kant’s "Critique of Judgement": He consequently defines ‘the symbolic’ as the horizon for a reflective approach based on empirical findings – and not as the foundation of a systematic derivation of the diversity of culture in the style of the idealistic tradition.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCulturexPhilosophy. 4aCassirer. 4aKant. 4aPluralität der Kultur. 4aPluralität der Wissenschaft. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aCassirer.  aKant.  aPlurality of Culture.  aPlurality of Science.1 aHobbs, D.J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishz978311075415508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021z9783110753929oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831106077580 cprintz978311060702440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311062363540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110623635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110623635/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075415-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV